@paulorb No this change will not effect that.  The response from a next command is negligable, the current parser will handle it perfectly because slices will not be copying strings and indexing will be fast.  This fix will only effect larger responses.

I think what you are experiencing is a problem with the way the responses are be gathered in gdbcontroller.py.  If you try setting a sleep before reading the streams it should stop it spinning and let the multiprocess do its work.  There is probably a cleaner way to deal with this but I'd have to look up the python docs which I can't don't have time to do right now.

in https://github.com/cs01/pygdbmi/blob/master/pygdbmi/gdbcontroller.py#L240 just before the try inside the while loop add time.sleep(0.1), or in the windows section if you are on windows I guess.

