```

Valgrind results with `val.bash` show no significant errors in Python 3.5 (and not from NumExpr) and a lot in 3.6.

Only leak from NumExpr in Py3.5 is on thread creation, but that's deliberate as we don't recreate threads after the first call.

[val_py35.txt](https://github.com/pydata/numexpr/files/1198435/val_py35.txt)

Many errors in Py3.6, many around the `ast`, `pickle`, and `marshal` library.  There's only one in NumExpr on a dealloc.

